value.value: The posterior lateral line ganglion develops from a cranial ectodermal placode and contains sensory neurons that innervate the posterior lateral line system.
Dorsolateral placode that gives rise to the anterior lateral line.
Sublingual that is the single element resulting from the fusion of the sublingual dorsal ossification and sublingual ventral ossification.
Supradorsals are small paired nodules of cartilage positioned at the distal ends of neural arches and the proximal end of neural spines (Arratia et al., 2001).

label.value: nucleus of the tract of the postoptic commissure

value.value: The nucleus containing the cell bodies of neurons whose axons form the postoptic commissure.
A zone of delayed differentiation at the midbrainhindbrain boundary. The IZ separates midbrain from anterior hindbrain neuronal clusters and has been described in all vertebrates. Geling et al, 2003.
Basiventrals are bilaterally paired cartilages lateral to the notochord which are replaced by ossified parapophyses or hemal arches.
Anatomical cluster that consists of supraneural 2 bone and supraneural 3 bone and their extensions, and which is part of the Weberian apparatus.
Hemal spines are extensions of hemal arches in the ventral skeletogenous septum of the caudal region.

Epibranchials 1-3 in adults are compound elements formed by the fusion of epibranchial cartilages and the so-called uncinate processes. Posteromedially directed uncinate processes develop on the posterior edge of epibranchials 1-3. These appear as separate centers of chondrification (6.2 mm) that later fuse laterally to the posterior edges of the epibranchial cartilages (6.8 mm).

label.value: epithelial mesenchymal boundary of regenerating fin/limb

value.value: An epithelial-mesenchymal boundary that is part of a regenerating fin/limb.
An epithelium that is part of a regenerating fin/limb.
The anteror lateral line ganglia develops from cranial ectodermal placodes and contain sensory neurons that innervate the anterior lateral line system.
Parapophysis that is the lateral projections from the first centrum in cyprinids, absent in catostomids, and absent in characiphysans (Fink and Fink, 1996).
Parapophysis that is lateral projection from the second centrum, absent in Siluriformes (Fink and Fink, 1996).
Neural arch 3 is expanded and fused to supraneural 3 as part of a neural complex roofing and protecting the neural canal.
Neural arch 4 is expanded and fused to supraneural 3 as part of the neural complex. A reduced neural spine projects from the posterior margin of the neural complex.
The parapophysis + rib, fused to the centrum, extends laterally then angles anteroventrally. A thin plate, the os suspensorium fuses to its median surface.
Posterior to the Weberian apparatus, otophysan supraneurals form as median, unpaired, rod- or platelike elements, as in other actinopterygians.

Dermal bone that first appears as paired ossifications in the membrane (dermis) dorsolateral to the ethmoid cartilage and anterolateral to the lateral ethmoids, later having the appearance of one butterfly-shaped element. Fused to the anterodorsal margin of the mesethmoid. Bordered anteriorly by the kinethmoid and posteriorly by the frontal.
Small rounded to egg-shaped cartilage bone that sits in an anterolateral depression on the prevomer. Articulates with the autopalatine in all cypriniforms.
Sesamoid bone located in the premaxillary-ethmoid ligament, between the mesethmoid and the premaxilla. The kinethmoid is an unpaired median bone.

definition.value: The kinethmoid is part of the protrusion mechanism of the upper jaw and is restricted to cypriniform fishes.

value.value: Infraorbital that is the second bone of the infraorbital series.
Infraorbital that is the third bone of the infraorbital series.
Infraorbital that is the fourth bone of the infraorbital series.

Endochondral bone that borders that medial edge of the posttemporal fossa. The epiotics are sutured to parietals and supraoccipital dorsally, the exoccipitals ventrally and the pterotics laterally. The epiotic is a paired bone.
Pelvic fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.
Pelvic fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.
